notesStmt.note: Imperfect at the beginning and at the end.
Most of the folios are more or less damaged (the best preserved part of the volume being folio 70-113).Modern restoration, stuck on paper.
Yesh῾ayah ben Tsaliḥ ben ῾Azaryahu (and also of Or 2554): inscribed, folio 87r.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: The commentary of Japheth ben Ali ha-Levi on the books of Daniel, Ezra-Nehemiah and Chronicles (fragments).

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 12 15; written lines: 12 15; The vowel-points and accents are supplied in red ink.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: A Naskhi hand of the 11th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine: 'Daniel, Ezra, Nehemiah, Chronicles, with Commentary. Hebrew and Arabic. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2556.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 08 July 1882, folio [130v].
